On my first day in Hanoi, I was determined to get a hand-carved stamp. While walking to the store I had originally bookmarked, we walked passed this small open room with wooden stamps and mooncake molds on display. No one was watching over the store … just these beautiful pieces of art out in the open for all to admire. About 15 minutes later, Ông Phạm Văn Quang comes out from the door inside and starts showing me how to pose with his stamps. We then spent the next hour and a half learning about his life, his profession of 40+ years, and ordering a custom wooden stamp to be picked up two days later. I truly felt like it was destiny that led me to meet him and have these wonderful conversations and experiences.

i’ve always been infatuated with the moon and i’ve always loved lanterns and eating cake … so naturally, one of my favorite holidays growing up was tết trung thu, or the harvest moon festival. when i was in hanoi, i had a mission to get a custom hand-carved wooden stamp made, and the craftsman i went to turned out to be a mooncake mold craftsman. (although he felt more like a shifu lol). he has been carving mooncake molds for over 40 years and each one felt so unique and full of life. i ended up taking a few home with me despite how heavy they were.

Introducing a new space for the next generation, in the neighborhood that raised them. A space to sit, think, drink … @loiloi.space ♥︎

Coming soon to Little Saigon, California 

—

Little did I know that coming home to California from Vietnam to celebrate Tết with my family in 2020 would lead to me to starting @loiloi.space three years later. 

Before I came back to California, I had just eased into a new chapter of my life in Saigon. I discovered my love for art direction and photography, became friends with people I now consider family, learned more about myself and my identity, and traveled all over my motherland. So coming back to California felt like utter whiplash. I was in denial for so long about having to leave behind this life I built up in my head. Yet somewhere along all that chaos, I rediscovered my dream to open up a coffee shop, and decided that if the universe brought me back home it was for a reason and I had to make it make sense. I started learning all that could about coffee, working part-time at a coffee shop as a barista, and planning to one day open my own shop. 

Three years later, I’m unbelievably thrilled to share with you all my baby, LôiLôi. There’s still so much I have to do, and so much that is to come. But I am blessed to have had an amazing support system throughout this journey. Y’all know who you are. And I’m ready to show the world all that is me and all that is LôiLôi.

One week ago I introduced to the world @loiloi.space ♥︎ Since then I’ve been struggling with what to share with y’all next … I’ve been waiting and waiting for over a year to release this secret, and now that it’s out, I’m at a loss for words. I am relieved … yet anxious … but for once, the stress I feel isn’t a bad kind of stress but rather, a stress that comes from pure excitement. My heart is overflowing from all the love and support you all have shown me and I’m giddy to finally be able to bring y’all along with me on this journey. I’m working 1000x harder so I can bring lôilôi to you guys sooner. Until then, thank you for being patient and here’s some photos of me in Vietnam secretly working on lôilôi 🫣

1. Learning about tea and visiting tea farms in Pleiku

Before the Year of the Tiger ends, I had this crazy idea to turn @loiloi.space’s currently empty store into a cozy makeshift coffee shop and host a last minute Tết celebration for close friends and family. I wanted them to see the space before construction begins and fill it up with lots of warmth and love. 

I honestly was a bit worried I was being too ambitious and spontaneous with all of this … but the Year of the Tiger is about risk-taking, and we managed to make it happen!!! 

Thank you Eddie, Josh, Tommy, Sam, Manh, Dany, Zoe, Nick, Riley, Emmi, Chichi, Nam, and chi Trang for helping me make this possible. Thank you to my cousins at Vans Bakery and the whole VB family. Thank you to the Lab Saigon. Thank you to my parents for believing in their crazy child. And thank you all for your love and support. This is only the beginning! 

There’s so much more left to come ♥︎

This past week has been pretty rough on my mental health as a first time business owner … but every time I’ve felt stressed and overwhelmed with @loiloi.space, I try to look towards my ancestors for strength. 

If my grandparents and parents could survive a war, leave their motherland and everything they had behind, cross an ocean on a boat, stay in refugee camps not knowing what was going to happen next, and then start a new life in a foreign country from the ground up … we truly can do anything we set our minds to. 

So hug your parents tight, call your ông bà, and take them out for a coffee date. My grandparents are all watching me from above now, but oh how I wish they were here to see me start my first business. ♥︎

Through my love of bringing people together, drinking coffee, eating delicious food, and indulging in art and entertainment … I came up with the idea of Lôilôi’s Breakfast Club - an event for the community, during the daytime, in celebration of Vietnamese culture and cuisine. 

Lôilôi is a coffee shop and concept space. A space to sit, think, drink. A space for the next generation in the neighborhood that raised them. My goal with Lôilôi has always been to bring people together and share the beauty of our heritage and culture with the world. Lôilôi’s Breakfast Club will be the perfect taste of that! 

Over the past few months, I’ve been stressing myself out on how to bring Lôilôi to you all while in the middle of figuring many issues that come with opening a business for the first time. As I was planning my first pop-up, a friend reached out and suggested I apply for RECONVENE Accelerator, a program designed to provide direct support to emerging creators who build communities and shape culture. So I filled it out and hoped for the best. A few weeks later, here we are as a top 25 finalist!

But we need your vote and your support! Please help me make this dream a reality and vote for me daily until July 25th! sweet behind the scenes moments from our lôilôi breakfast club promo shoot ♥︎ 

i’ve always been one to feel the most calm when i’m surrounded by water - perhaps it’s because i was raised in a beach town or perhaps it’s because i have so many pisces placements (lol). but for whatever reason, being next to a body of water has always been important to me. 

with this shoot, i wanted to bring together elements from my life here and my life in vietnam. i wanted to create this fairytale-like dreamscape where we could go and drink coffee, eat fruit and moon cakes, breathe in the fresh air, take in all the foliage around us, and simply exist in this wonderful space …

and honestly, i think we did just that. 

more to come, on here and on @loiloi.space ♥︎ so please stay tuned and continue to look out for more information on lôilôi breakfast club 😚

someone asked me the other day why i have so many photos saved on my phone, and for me, the answer is quite simple: i want to remember. remember those moments, who i was with, what i was feeling. remembering what was there before me and who will come after me. 

there are so many days where i feel stuck and unsure of what to do next … and on those days i end up falling into a rabbit hole of nostalgia. i look back on these past trips in search of the spark i felt in those moments and realize that so many people have experienced that same similar fleeting moment and so many …. have yet to. 

traveling around the motherland has always felt that way to me. where there’s never enough time to spend in one place … yet hundreds, if not thousands, of other places to see and experience. 

so i guess what i’m trying to say is if it seems like i’m going crazy over lôilôi and our breakfast club event, i want to make sure that i am able to somehow portray and express these feelings and moments to y’all and share all that is beautiful and wonderful of the place i call my motherland. 🥹 

love y’all, always.

as a kid, i remember dressing up in traditional vietnamese clothing on all the major vietnamese holidays and going to school with little treats and a presentation to share with my class (completely unannounced and unbeknownst to the teacher LOL).

looking back, it’s kinda crazy how some of the things we do as kids all makes sense in our adulthood - whether it’s through our personalities, our passions, our careers, etc. 

thank you for being part of the first ever lôilôi breakfast club. this experience was so special and so dear to my heart, i’m in awe of you all and in disbelief that it’s over. you guys have made my heart so incredibly overwhelmed with joy. i was so busy running around during the event, but in those small pockets of time where i could just stand and take in everything that was in front of me, all i could think in my head was “wow, this is all i ever wanted.” 

thank you for having this experience with me. thank you for coming into our home, meeting our family, and being part of the family. thank you for being open to experiencing a glimpse of my home, my heart, and my culture. and thank you for really just believing in me and my vision with lôilôi. 

this is only the beginning, y’all. hẹn gặp lại nhe? 

lots … and lots … of posts coming your way this week lol hope y’all aren’t tired of my content yet 😵‍💫

earlier this summer i entered the @eventbrite RECONVENE accelerator program with my idea of the lôilôi breakfast club.

i had no prior experience in throwing an event to this scale … tbh, all i knew going into this competition was that i wanted to bring people together and i wanted to bring lôilôi coffee to all of y’all that have been waiting so patiently for us. 

fast forward a few months later, i ended up winning the program and was finally able to begin the process of making my dream and my vision come to life. 

it’s crazy how the universe listens to you if you ask and how the red strings of fate brings the people you need in your life to you. 

i’m in awe of this team and the way we were able to pull this event off in only a month and a half of planning. i look at them in disbelief sometimes because i know i have crazy ideas and yet, they’ve been so patient and so dedicated in helping me bring these ideas to fruition. it’s not easy, but finding them has made lôilôi bloom into so much more than i could ever imagine. 

this is partially what lôilôi is all about. highlighting these beautiful people and sharing their talents and capabilities to the world as we come together in celebration of our heritage and identities. 

and from this experience, i know that no matter what, we’re able to figure things out together and everything just naturally comes to life through our efforts. 

i am the most blessed and i feel so much love bc of them. this team was built off a dream and it’s through the mutual trust, respect, and admiration for one another that we’ve come this far in such a short amount of time.

being born and raised in california, i never had the chance to see the seasons change. it was something i always longed for, something that was always on my list of things to experience. this trip fulfilled that wish of mine. and so, it’s safe to say i fell in love and there’s nothing quite it 🤧🤎

new york city has always been a place of “almost” to me. i “almost” made my way there but never seemed to have an opportunity to stay. but still, new york was the place i yearned to be in for as long as i can remember. and now it seems like the universe is granting me this wish 🤭

@yaoybl and i first met in a business class during our UCI days, so it’s crazy to see us both starting our businesses at the same time. over the past year, while working on @loiloi.space, i’ve simultaneously been working with Yao on @yingtaonyc as his art director and creative consultant. we recruited @bluefintuna.le and @thelabsaigon and the rest is history 🍒🖤

last week, we held a pre-opening party to invite guests into our space, meet the team, and enjoy a teaser of our food and drinks. i could not be more proud of Yao for making Yingtao come to life and i am so excited for what’s to come. 

thank you everyone who’s been part of this journey and will continue this journey with us!! i am so thankful to be part of such an amazing team. 🥺❤️ 2024 is going to be a crazy one for sure. see you soon, new york. stay warm and cozy till then! 🍒🖤 謝謝大家、很想你們。我很快回來！

the feeling when you’re back in the motherland and everything starts to make sense again 😌

2022 was a year of learning, growing, and developing with @loiloi.space 

it was important for me to start this journey in vietnam … and so, i made two trips back. we spent a few months simply traveling up and down the country, going to coffee shops, sightseeing, visiting coffee farms and tea plantations, learning traditional vietnamese forms of art, having meetings with my branding and design team @thelabsaigon, and doing all sorts of rnd. 

2023 then became the year of seeing everything come to fruition. my heart has been on a rollercoaster with all the ups and downs we faced; yet throughout it all, i feel so blessed. seeing all this love for lôilôi and being able to share my culture and heritage has given me so much meaning. i’m able to do the things i do because of y’all, and it’s been an honor to have you guys alongside with me. (hope y’all continue to stay bahaha) 

i can’t wait to share with y’all what we have planned next. 😩❣️

for now, these are some clips from our trip in 2022. excited for what’s to come over the next few months in vietnam. ☕️🛵💨

Introducing our new concept, LÔILÔI SUNSET CLUB, at @bakes.saigon 🥂

Sunset Club is a flirtier take on Breakfast Club. It’s a holiday cocktail party with drinks, light bites, music, and karaoke. It’s a place to get to know people, have conversations, and truly embrace the holiday spirit. 

Growing up in America, I always loved watching holiday romcoms. I loved how silly and absurd they were. I loved the corniness and insane romantic gestures. Perhaps it’s the hopeless romantic in me or perhaps, it’s because I longed to experience these stereotypical cinematic holiday moments. 

When I told @bluefintuna.le and @laure_chevallier I would be in Saigon this year, we immediately decided we had to do a @bakes.saigon x @loiloi.space collab. And since it’s the holidays I figured now would be the time to experience this “Caffeinated Christmas Romcom” for myself and share that with y’all through Sunset Club. 

So, join us on December 9th from 4:30PM to 8:30PM at Bakes in Thao Dien ✨

We did it 🥹❤️ Lôilôi Breakfast Club made it to Saigon!!

My dream has always been to bridge the gap between Little Saigon and Saigon - to express myself as a Vietnamese American who loves her motherland while, at the same time, wanting to share with the world her identity and culture. 

The fundamental mission of Lôilôi Breakfast Club is to bring people together, have conversations over coffee, and learn more about each other and Vietnamese culture. So doing a Breakfast Club in Vietnam felt surreal. 

After my first event in LA, I mentioned to @bluefintuna.le that I’d be coming to Vietnam at the end of the year. He suggested I bring Breakfast Club back to Saigon and do it at @bakes.saigon with @laure_chevallier 

At first I thought he was crazy, I had just gone through the most insane whirlwind experience and I needed a vacation … but … Obviously I said “yes, let’s absolutely do it.” 🥰 And so, the Lôilôi x Bakes: A Caffeinated Christmas Rom Com began. 

My heart is filled with so much joy (and so much caffeine). This experience has been incredible. There’s so much I still want to say and so much I still need to share, but as always, I am still processing and going through all the post-event motions!! “Thank you” post coming soon. “Sunset Club” coming soon. Behind the scenes coming soon. Much more coming soon. Just stay tuned for more 😭❤️ 

Love y’all and so thankful!! 🥹

2023 has been a year of developing and growing with @loiloi.space, spending more time with loved ones, learning more about myself, traveling with my parents to greece for the first time, working on @yingtaonyc, going back to new york for the first time in a couple years, and spending the last few months in vietnam doing what i love with the people i love 🥹❤️ i’m so grateful for being here. i’m so happy!!!!! i love y’all forreal 🥰

a look back on all the memories and milestones of 2023 🥹🖤 

reflecting back on everything that has happened this year, it’s safe to say that i am so blessed. this year has been a year of self-growth and realization. i’ve learned so much after starting @loiloi.space and developing alongside with it. who would’ve thought that we’d go from building a coffee shop to winning the @eventbrite reconvene accelerator program and starting lôilôi breakfast club and bringing that to vietnam?surround yourself with people who encourage you but also aren’t afraid to tell you the truth and help you grow. i’ve learned that our energy must be cherished and to spend time with those who love you and can also match your energy and effort. i’m so lucky to have the best support system of family, friends, mentors, and loved ones. i wouldn’t be here without y’all. 

i used to be so scared of the future but this year has taught me that that way of thinking is so silly! life may seem scary, but it doesn’t make sense to be scared because you don’t know what the outcome may be till it happens. so as long as you’re trying, things will work out one way or another. life is ultimately way too short to be worrying so much about the what ifs. the universe is good, it listens if you let it. pappa loi also always says that it’s not about the destination, it’s about the journey. enjoy the process and trust in yourself. 

i feel like i am now entering this era where i trust in everything that is happening. i believe in what im doing, in myself, and the people i am with. i know this coming year is going to be the best 🥹 everything that i’ve been working hard on developing this year will come to fruition in 2024. thank you for being here alongside me. thank you for supporting me and my visions. thank you for believing in lôilôi. thank you for existing. let’s go harder and be better in 2024 nhe mọi người oiiii 🥰❤️ 

with love, 
victoria hoàng-vi loi aka vi aka vic aka your favorite việt kiều who loves vietnam with all her heart 🤧

A small glimpse of our first year as lôilôi ♥︎ Thank you for being here and for being part of this journey with us. Vi và team lôilôi muốn rất cảm ơn mọi người đã bên cạnh mình năm nay. Năm 2024 lôilôi sẽ có nhiều cơ hội để gặp mọi người nhé ☺️

Looking back on 2023, I feel so blessed to have this year as our first year with lôilôi. Every day we are growing and learning more and more about who we are and what we want to share with the world. We started off as a coffee shop and concept space located in the heart of Little Saigon, California. We were founded off my identity as the daughter of Vietnamese refugees who loves her motherland so much that she wants to share her culture and heritage to the world through this creative space. We ran into some inevitable circumstances with construction, which led us to trying to find other outlets of getting our coffee to y’all. So spontaneously, we entered the @eventbrite reconvene accelerator program, won $20,000 from it, and made Lôilôi Breakfast Club happen!! We then were able to bring Breakfast Club to Vietnam for the first time and introduce a new concept of Sunset Club. And now we’re working and planning on bigger and brighter things for 2024!! 🥰 

So thank you, again. Thank you, always.

happy baby in her mom’s hometown for the first time!!! con về quê của mẹ nè 🥰 

i grew up listening to stories of my mom’s childhood - the house she grew up in with her siblings, the streets she’d walk up and down on, the fields where she’d fight crickets with her friends, the trips to the beach, ông ngoại’s store and all of his endeavors. these memories became my daydreams, a world and its entirety in my imagination. 

and now, after so many years of traveling and even living in vietnam, this was the year that i felt like i needed to make a trip to phan rang. something inside me was calling me back, and i am so glad i did. there was something so special about it- this overwhelming feeling of familiarity. almost like a warm embrace from my ancestors, but at the same time just imagining how proud my grandpa would be seeing his granddaughter in the city he left so long ago is a crazy thought. it’s even crazier seeing the similarities of phan rang and where and i grew up. it’s in the way there’s a slight saltiness to the air, a gentle ocean breeze, the way the waves crash along the shore, the sand dunes and rocky mountains, the bonfires at night under all the stars, the friendliness of the locals and the distance of the city to the beach. from little things to big things, everything made sense and made my heart warm. 

now that i’ve been once, i can easily say i’m ready to go again and again. i can’t wait to come back and spend more time here, especially with my parents and family one day. 😖🤍
